  "title": "Accounts cum HR Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Maintain accounts using <strong>QuickBooks</strong> (accounts payable/receivable, bank reconciliation, reporting).</p></li><li><p>Handle payroll, CPF contributions, and employee records in compliance with Singapore labor laws.</p></li><li><p>Manage recruitment, onboarding, and HR administration.</p></li><li><p>Support sales with order processing, invoicing, and customer follow-ups.</p></li><li><p>Manage procurement including purchase requests, vendor coordination, and stock monitoring.</p></li><li><p>Perform ad hoc duties as assigned.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Diploma or Bachelor’s degree in Commerce, Business, HR, or related field.</p></li><li><p>2–5 years experience in accounting and HR (experience in electronics/semiconductor preferred).</p></li><li><p>Proficient in <strong>QuickBooks</strong> and MS Excel.</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of Singapore labor laws, CPF, and GST compliance.</p></li><li><p>Self-motivated, organized, and able to manage multiple functions independently.</p></li></ul>",
